1. Configure Git (First Time Setup)

git config --global user.name "Kaushal"
git config --global user.email "kaushal@example.com"

Check config:

git config --list

2. Create a Repository
Create New Folder + Initialize Git
mkdir myproject
cd myproject
git init

3. Check Status
git status

4. Add Files
Add Single File
git add app.py
Add All Files
git add .

5. Commit Changes
git commit -m "Added login feature"

6. View Commit History
git log

Short version:

git log --oneline


7. Clone Existing GitHub Repository
git clone https://github.com/user/project.git

8. Connect Local Repo to GitHub
Add Remote Repository
git remote add origin https://github.com/user/repo.git

Check remote:

git remote -v

9. Push Code to GitHub
First Push
git push -u origin main
Normal Push After That
git push

10. Pull Latest Code
git pull

12. Branch Commands

Create Branch

git branch feature-login
Switch Branch
git checkout feature-login

OR modern command:

git switch feature-login
Create + Switch Together
git checkout -b feature-login



13. Merge Branch

Go to main branch:

git checkout main

Merge:

git merge feature-login
14. Delete Branch
git branch -d feature-login


5. Undo Changes
Undo Unstaged Changes
git restore file.txt
Remove from Staging
git restore --staged file.txt
16. Remove File
git rm file.txt

Commit after removing:

git commit -m "Removed file"
17. Rename File
git mv old.txt new.txt
18. Check Difference
git diff
19. Ignore Files

Create .gitignore

Example:

node_modules/
*.log
.env
